D. Acquisition Strategy
The Imaging and Targeting Support efforts are prioritized on an annual basis by the GCWG in accordance with documented AF ISR gaps, ISR Planning and
Programming Guidance (IP2G), and operational partner inputs. The resulting funded efforts are then contracted for and/or executed by various program offices,
laboratories, industry, and/ or other government agencies.

The acquisition strategy is to maximize commercial and national development efforts and investment while reducing acquisition timelines through multiple contracting
methods. This includes the use of Engineering Change Proposals to modify existing and new contracts that were awarded both competitively and on a sole source
basis.




