Title: Advanced Maritime Defense Technologies Concepts                                                                                   6.688                -              -
Description: The Advanced Maritime Defense Technologies Concepts program explored novel technologies and concepts of
operations to mature capabilities that extend freedom of access, operations, and homeland defense in all parts of the maritime
domain, including waterways, arctic areas, and the seabed. The program investigated and matured technologies necessary for
Unmanned Underwater Vehicle (UUV) and Unmanned Surface Vessel (USV) concepts for autonomous operation and domain
specific warfare. Enabling technologies for advanced undersea systems, including a revolutionary propulsion concept, and novel
approaches for maritime platform and fixed location self-defense were investigated. Novel technologies and concepts required
for arctic and seabed operations, such as distributed sensing, navigation, and communications architectures, as well as including
new technologies to enable long duration maritime platforms were also investigated. Finally, future concepts, approaches, and
techniques were identified to enable contested environment operations utilizing unmanned maritime platforms.

