D. Acquisition Strategy
The VIRGINIA Class Submarine Program has implemented Integrated Product and Process Development (IPPD). The traditional distinct phasing of the design process
has been replaced with the continuous concurrent engineering IPPD process. The IPPD approach has facilitated a smoother transition from design to manufacturing and
has reduced the number of changes typically encountered during construction of the lead and early follow-on ships. The Program Office is currently managing two Multi-
Year Procurement (MYP) contracts. The first is for the Block IV (FY14-18) ships awarded April 2014. The second is for the Block V (FY19-23) ships, which incorporate
Acoustic Superiority (AS) modifications and Virginia Payload Module (VPM).




