Title: Force Protection                                                                                                    7.517         6.230       5.890      0.000       5.890
Description: This activity investigates new ways and means to protect forces and materiel across all domain
threats in all operational settings, from contested maritime, air, and land domains, to include complex urban
environments. The portfolio protects against adversaries' challenges such as guided-rockets and missiles,
mobile coastal artillery, threat electronic warfare, and counter intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance, and
waterborne threats from ports, harbors, and in the littorals. Mines and obstacles, both in the water and ashore,
also complicate amphibious operations. The activity invests in vehicle survivability aspects that are exacerbated
due to size, weight, power, and cost constraints inherent to Marine Corps operations and the harsh nature of
maritime environments.

