sensors for counter tactical surveillance, active protection, signature management, and exploration of
expeditionary undersea warfare capabilities. This activity also considers technology for payloads, packages
and sensors that are needed by amphibious vehicles (both manned and unmanned) including mine counter
measures; explosive hazard defeat systems; and obstacle and threat detection systems as well as technologies
for improved protection for individuals against blast, ballistic and blunt impact threats.

FY 2025 Plans:
- Continue research to enable technologies for countering unmanned aerial vehicles. The effort will address both
an increase in number and sophistication of threat systems to include kinetic and/or controlled interceptors with a
