Research

 This Program Element (PE) funds Applied Research, which is the systematic study to understand the means to meet a recognized and specific need. Most of the work in
 this PE can be classified between Technology Readiness Level (TRL) 2 (technology concept and/or application formulation) and TRL 4 (component and/or breadboard
 validation in laboratory environments).

 Due to the number of efforts in this PE, the programs described herein are representative and not exhaustive of the work included in this PE.

 Beginning in FY 2026, Research Areas have been identified for the Focus Areas within the S&T budget. These new Research Areas aim to better align the efforts in the
 Focus Area to allow visibility into the specific challenges and the approaches to alleviate those challenges.

