FY 2024 Accomplishments: Conduct research to investigate power electronics building blocks.

Continue to build and test power electronics building blocks (PEBBs) for modular and scalable power converter
applications. The building block will be a standard and flexible module for various applications including state-
of-the-art solid-state transformers. The effort will focus on advanced PCB design, manufacturing techniques,
and material capabilities that would result in a standard PEBB module and platform from which to enter full-
scale production. Advanced thermal management methods for effective cooling will be evaluated and integrated
into the PCB system to achieve desirable power levels and improved power density while maintaining design
modularity and flexibility.
