MALE will support MQ-9A capability and payloads/sensors primary hardware development, Non-Recurring
Engineering (NRE), capability integration studies, design work and Air Vehicle and Ground Control Station
integration. MALE will also support programmatic, engineering, logistics, technical requirements generation,
development test and full integration of payloads/sensors into the system. The program will perform payload
development and capability improvements, to include platform and payload software development and test,
required to pace evolving threats.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
MALE will support MQ-9A capability and payloads/sensors integration and continued development, Non-
Recurring Engineering (NRE), design work, software upgrades, and Air Vehicle and Ground Control Station
integration. MALE will also support programmatic, engineering, logistics, test, software baseline development
and technical requirements refinement in support of spiral development and integration of payloads/sensors into
the system required to pace evolving threats.
