D. Acquisition Strategy
The MALE sensor acquisition strategy leverages existing developmental programs with mature technology readiness level (TRL) Airborne Network Extension (ANE)/
SkyTower II, Electronic Warfare (EW), and Detect And Avoid System (DAAS) capabilities for transition and integration on the MQ-9A UAS. The MALE capabilities
(payloads/sensor) acquisition strategy uses organic government resources, competitive and sole-source contract awards, and assisted acquisition approaches, Middle
Tier Acquisition and Other Transaction Agreements to develop, integrate, and acquire the discrete capabilities.




