Title: Machine Learning with Constrained Resources                                                                         4.500       4.602           -           -          -
Description: This effort will research new ML and reinforcement learning methods to address issues of
statistically mismatched and incomplete information which must be annotated, collected, classified, and used for
rapid decisions by joint intelligent agent-human teams. In addition, multi-modal human interaction approaches
will be investigated to ensure effective Soldier interactions and understanding of intent. The goal of this research
is to enable joint human-intelligent agent decision making, optimizing the strengths of each in the decision
process and creating an adaptive, agile team. This work applies research conducted in PE 0611102A (Defense
Research Sciences) / AA6 (Robotics and Mobile Energy) and AA9 (Information and Networking).

